    "id": 23697,
    "title": "Opinion Announcement - March 04, 2014",
    "transcript": {
        "title": null,
        "duration": 309.504,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 309.504,
                "byte_start": 105472,
                "byte_stop": 0,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 6.712,
                        "byte_start": 105472,
                        "byte_stop": 132326,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 6.712,
                                "byte_start": 105472,
                                "byte_stop": 132326,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has our opinion in case 12-5196 Law versus Siegel."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 6.712,
                        "stop": 309.504,
                        "byte_start": 132326,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 6.712,
                                "stop": 12.822,
                                "byte_start": 132326,
                                "byte_stop": 156776,
                                "text": "This case is here on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals from the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.822,
                                "stop": 18.682,
                                "byte_start": 156776,
                                "byte_stop": 180287,
                                "text": "The petitioner Steven Law filed for Chapter 7 bankruptcy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.682,
                                "stop": 34.902,
                                "byte_start": 180287,
                                "byte_stop": 245175,
                                "text": "He valued his California home at roughly $360,000 and he claimed that $75,000 of its value was covered by California\u0027s homestead exception and thus was except from the bankruptcy estate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.902,
                                "stop": 47.743,
                                "byte_start": 245175,
                                "byte_stop": 296479,
                                "text": "The Federal Bankruptcy Law allows an individual to use either a federal homestead exception or a state homestead exception, he had chosen California\u0027s."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.743,
                                "stop": 60.291,
                                "byte_start": 296479,
                                "byte_stop": 346739,
                                "text": "He also claimed that the home was subject to two liens including one in favor of someone named Lili Lin, L-I-L-I L-I-N."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.291,
                                "stop": 66.247,
                                "byte_start": 346739,
                                "byte_stop": 370563,
                                "text": "The respondent Alfred Siegel was the trustees of Law\u0027s bankruptcy estate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.247,
                                "stop": 84.251,
                                "byte_start": 370563,
                                "byte_stop": 442556,
                                "text": "He challenged the Lili Lin lien in an adversary proceeding but found himself drawn into protracted and expensive litigation with someone claiming to be Lili Lin."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.251,
                                "stop": 102.04,
                                "byte_start": 442556,
                                "byte_stop": 513714,
                                "text": "Five years later, the Bankruptcy Court ruled that the Lili Lin lien was a fiction invented by Law to protect his home from creditors and that the legal papers supposedly filed from China by Lili Lin had most likely been filed by Law himself."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.04,
                                "stop": 122.732,
                                "byte_start": 513714,
                                "byte_stop": 596470,
                                "text": "The Court then granted Siegel\u0027s motion to surcharge Law\u0027s $75,000 homestead exception making those funds available to defray the hundreds of thousands of dollars in attorney\u0027s fees that Siegel had incurred in overcoming Law\u0027s fraudulent misrepresentations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.732,
                                "stop": 130.464,
                                "byte_start": 596470,
                                "byte_stop": 627399,
                                "text": "The Ninth Circuit Bankruptcy Appellate Panel and the Ninth Circuit affirmed we granted certiorari."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.464,
                                "stop": 136.089,
                                "byte_start": 627399,
                                "byte_stop": 649864,
                                "text": "Siegel argues that the surcharge order was justified under two sources of authority."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.089,
                                "stop": 151.875,
                                "byte_start": 649864,
                                "byte_stop": 712976,
                                "text": "First, he relies on a statute 11 U. S. C. Section 104(a) which says that a Bankruptcy Court may issue any order that is necessary or appropriate to carry out the provisions of the Bankruptcy Code."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.875,
                                "stop": 161.831,
                                "byte_start": 712976,
                                "byte_stop": 752891,
                                "text": "Second, he points to the inherent power of courts to sanction abusive litigation conduct."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 161.831,
                                "stop": 173.449,
                                "byte_start": 752891,
                                "byte_stop": 799284,
                                "text": "But when a Bankruptcy Court acts under either Section 105(a) or its inherent powers, it may not take any action that is prohibited by statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.449,
                                "stop": 187.37,
                                "byte_start": 799284,
                                "byte_stop": 854977,
                                "text": "As relevant here, the Bankruptcy Code provides that except property including homestead exception is not liable for any administrative expense which includes a trustee\u0027s attorney\u0027s fees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 187.37,
                                "stop": 195.026,
                                "byte_start": 854977,
                                "byte_stop": 885593,
                                "text": "When the Bankruptcy Court ordered that the except equity in Law\u0027s home be used to pay Siegel\u0027s attorney\u0027s fees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 195.026,
                                "stop": 199.086,
                                "byte_start": 885593,
                                "byte_stop": 901893,
                                "text": "It violated that clear statutory prohibition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 199.086,
                                "stop": 208.864,
                                "byte_start": 901893,
                                "byte_stop": 940972,
                                "text": "Siegel argues when that a debtor engages in misconduct, the Bankruptcy Court can deny the debtor an exception to which he otherwise he would have been entitled."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 208.864,
                                "stop": 211.279,
                                "byte_start": 940972,
                                "byte_stop": 950690,
                                "text": "That argument is misplaced here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 211.279,
                                "stop": 217.101,
                                "byte_start": 950690,
                                "byte_stop": 973887,
                                "text": "It comes too late since Siegel did not raise a timely objection to Law\u0027s homestead exception."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 217.101,
                                "stop": 218.813,
                                "byte_start": 973887,
                                "byte_stop": 980783,
                                "text": "He was given at it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 218.813,
                                "stop": 227.281,
                                "byte_start": 980783,
                                "byte_stop": 1014638,
                                "text": "But even if he had objected, a Bankruptcy Court may not deny an exception on any ground not specified in the Bankruptcy Code."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 227.281,
                                "stop": 246.163,
                                "byte_start": 1014638,
                                "byte_stop": 1090184,
                                "text": "Section 522 of the Code exhaustively specifies the criteria that will entitle property to the homestead exception and it spells out a number of carefully calibrated exceptions and limitations including some that are based on the debtor\u0027s misconduct."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 246.163,
                                "stop": 251.069,
                                "byte_start": 1090184,
                                "byte_stop": 1109828,
                                "text": "Courts are not authorized to create additional exceptions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 251.069,
                                "stop": 265.435,
                                "byte_start": 1109828,
                                "byte_stop": 1167297,
                                "text": "When Congress crafted the detailed provisions of Section 522 it struck a balance between the interest of trustees and creditors and the interest of debtors and their dependence who inhabit the homestead."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 265.435,
                                "stop": 285.844,
                                "byte_start": 1167297,
                                "byte_stop": 1248904,
                                "text": "It is not for courts to alter the balance struck by the statute.Bankruptcy courts nonetheless retained ample authority to punish debtor misconduct in appropriate cases of dishonest debtor may be denied a discharge, he may be ordered to pay monetary sanctions, and even prosecuted criminally."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 285.844,
                                "stop": 302.901,
                                "byte_start": 1248904,
                                "byte_stop": 1317136,
                                "text": "But whatever other sanctions of Bankruptcy Court may impose on a dishonest debtor, it may not contravene express provisions of the Bankruptcy Code by ordering that except property be used to pay debts and expenses for which that property is not liable under the Code."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 302.901,
                                "stop": 307.083,
                                "byte_start": 1317136,
                                "byte_stop": 1333854,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit is reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 307.083,
                                "stop": 309.504,
                                "byte_start": 1333854,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Court\u0027s decision is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
